Source: giacpy
Maintainer: Frederic Han
Section: python
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: python-all-dev, python, debhelper (>= 7), python3-all-dev, python3, giac (>=1.1.3), libgmp-dev, qt5-default, qt5-qmake, libqt5svg5-dev
XB-Python-Version: ${python:Versions}
X-Python3-Version: >=3.0
Standards-Version: 3.8.4
Homepage: http://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~frederic.han/xcas/giacpy

Package: python-giacpy
Architecture: any
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: python-giacpy-qt
Description: A Cython frontend to the c++ library giac. (Computer Algebra System)
 .
   * giacpy is an interface to be able to use from Python the Giac features.
     It is built with cython.
 .
   * Giac is a general purpose Computer algebra system by Bernard Parisse released under GPLv3.
 .
      - http://www-fourier.ujf-grenoble.fr/~parisse/giac.html
      - It is build on C and C++ libraries: 
        PARI, NTL (advanced arithmetic functions), CoCoA (Groebner basis), GSL (numerics), 
        GMP (big integers), MPFR (big/multiprecision floats) 
      - It  provides (fast) algorithms for multivariate polynomial operations (product, GCD, factorisation) and
      - symbolic  computations: solver, simplifications, limits/series, integration, sommation...
      - Linear Algebra with numerical or symbolic coefficients.
 .

Package: python-giacpy-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: python-giacpy, ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Qt extention for graphic outputs
 .
   * giacpy is an interface to be able to use from Python the Giac (computer 
     algebra system) features.
 .
   * This Qt extension enable graphic outputs for giacpy via Qcas.
 .

